messages.messageBody:
==No one sits around discussing whether the fussy baby needs to nurse *right now* or not

and then decide "no" <g>.==

When my youngest was a baby and it was bedtime and my middle son wanted a book, I would ask him if he wanted me to read the book or nurse the baby first. He always said I should nurse the baby and he'd wait because he didn't want to hear the baby cry. Even now when we go to bed sometimes he tells me to give his little brother milk even if little brother doesn't ask for it.

Alysia
